HELP XCOLOURS                               Jonathan Meyer, June 27 1990

This file contains a list of all of the named colours contained in the X
Windows colour database. Many colours have different combinations of
spellings, capitalizations, word spacings etc. Each line represents one
colour, and shows each of that colour's possible spellings.

For facilities that allow you to use the Poplog Widget Set with
named colours, see REF * XpwCore/XpwSetColor.

NB: Colours that look good on one colour monitor may not look the same on
another. Be careful when choosing colours, making sure that it is always
possible for the user to redefine important colours.

Also note that the divisions into different shades listed here are only
a guideline - its best to view the colour to see what it looks like.

         CONTENTS - (Use <ENTER> g to access required sections)

